SQL Server Installation â€“ Prerequisites Notes
---------------------------------------------
1.  Supported Operating Systems

Windows Server 2022 / 2019 / 2016
Windows 11 / 10 (Developer/Express Editions)
Core editions supported (limited features)
Note: Check compatibility for your SQL Server version.

2. Hardware Requirements (Minimum)

Processor: 1.4 GHz 64-bit (2+ GHz recommended)
RAM: 2 GB (4 GB or more recommended)
Disk Space: 6 GB minimum (more for features/data)
Display: 800x600 resolution or higher

3. Software Requirements

.NET Framework 4.8 (or required by your SQL version)
Windows Installer 4.5+
PowerShell 5.1+
Visual C++ Redistributables (installed automatically if needed)

4. User Permissions

Local Administrator rights required
UAC should not block the installer

5. File System & Disk

NTFS (FAT32 not supported)
Enough space for:
SQL Binaries
TempDB
Databases
Backups & Logs

6. Network & Firewall

Default SQL port: TCP 1433
Browser service: UDP 1434
Open firewall ports if needed
Named instances may use dynamic ports

7. Features to Choose During Install

Database Engine Services
SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS)
Integration Services (SSIS)
Analysis Services (SSAS)
Full-Text Search, Client Tools, etc.

8. Authentication & Accounts

Choose Windows or Mixed Mode
Strong password for sa account if Mixed
Set SQL Server services to run with:
Default accounts or custom domain accounts

